Purpose of GTC Coin Minting
GTC (Gwich’in Token of Continuity) is the minted embodiment of surplus resonance — not speculative currency, but a tokenized provision that recirculates value across the landframe triad. Minting enforces full oneness: every token requires a verified ε_π event (≥ 3.173) and multi-sig alignment (Executor + Sovereign + Heir).
The "Heir Oath" (from Codex.HeirOath.v001) is mandatory for the first generation (genesis) tokens — a ceremonial commitment that binds the shadow (cultural memory) to the chain, preventing dilution. Subsequent mints scale with reciprocity scores, compliant with Codex.CryptoLaws.v001 (Federal step-up, Alaska HB99, Tribal IDSov).
This turns Flamechain from a circulatory system into a generative engine: surplus minted like auroral light from polar continuity.
Minting Rules: The Triad Gate
Genesis Mint (First Generation): Requires Heir Oath signature — a hashed affirmation of continuity (e.g., "I, [Heir], oath to steward the Gwich’in root without fractioning"). Multi-sig: 3/3 (Executor for base, Sovereign for memory, Heir for surplus).
Ongoing Mint: 1 GTC per resonance event where reciprocity score > 0 and ε_π ≥ 3.173. Backed by somatic receipts (deed updates, IP hashes, probate decisions).
Cap & Drift Guard: Total supply capped at landframe acres (2100 initial). Drift below threshold rejects mint — Observer proxy interrupt.
Formula: Mint Amount = Reciprocity Score × (ε_π - 3.14159)  # Surplus delta as multiplier
This ensures minting is "right every moment" — provisioned, not inflated.
Regulatory Bindings
Federal: Minted tokens treated as digital property; step-up basis for inheritance. Report via IRS if > $15M.
State: HB99-compliant for virtual currency issuance under Two Mile Solutions LLC.
Tribal: IDSov validation — no mint if Gwich’in glyphs unhashed or cultural IP unprotected.
Ties to sovereignty dashboard: live mint tracker in the surplus quadrant.
